name: Brad F
text: Order pick up all the time good topings and always ready when i get there. Crew is good. Spot me some sauce for my crust...thanks for the sauce.

name: Carol Swanburg
text: The pizza was sloppy and wet and dough didn't look cooked. Not what I was expecting from Papa Gino's which is usually the best! Also staff making pizza should wear gloves in my opinion.

name: ws01
text: Nice atmosphere, but what of it? Long wait time, 45 minutes. Once man came over w/pizza, he didn't even apologize and told us we now had our beautiful pizza. I didn't buy a pizza to look at it, I bought it to ate it...Did just that and was not pleased but not disgusted either. Not coming back again, likely.

name: Artem G
text: Too thin, too oily

name: Chuck Lynn
text: We Don’t live in the area and only come back annually and always stop at Gino’s. The staff was much nicer, more attentive and more professional at the location in Wilbraham MA

name: Erik Kadikis
text: Food it very good, especially if you can catch it on one of the 50% off days. Cheese pizza is ok, but the pizzas with toppings are amazing!

name: Tiffany West
text:
We love vernon
papa ginos
always delicious

name: Susan Howard
text: The food was ok. I got the hot veggie pocket. When I asked if they had A1 sauce they said no. The sandwich was dry without a sauce. They offered lettuce, tomato, and mayo.. yuck no. They have a steak pocket and are owned by the same group as D Angelos; who carries A1. Will have to go there nrxt time.

name: Kim Maura
text: This place is very nice and the food is excellent. The selection is good. Delicious!

text: Been going there for a long time,great pizza, i miss papa genos. I   have been living in san jose ca   for  7 years and  we  have  round table pizza  and mountain mikes  and i don"t like either one.I also miss bertuccis.

text: Wings are good thats it. Pizza is borderline edible and the mac n cheese I can still taste and smell the rotten cheese 2 days later.

name: big d
text: As a kid and young adult I loved Papa Gino's pizza.  I primarily used to get it from the one in the East Brook mall in Windham but occasionally remember getting it from here for lunch when I was on the road. …More

text: Every time I eat pizza from here I always without fail end up with horrible stomach aches and with issues in the bathroom. DO NOT EAT FROM HERE
